        public void addValue(java.lang.String value)
        Adds a String representation (value) of a value to this column object's values list. These values will come from each row of a ResultSet of a database query.
        Parameters:
        value - The column value to add to values

      • getValue

        public java.lang.String getValue(int i)
        Returns the column value at row index i. Note that the index starts at 0 so that getValue(0) will get the value for this column from the first row of a ResultSet.
        Parameters:
        i - The index of the column value to get
        Returns:
        The String representation of the value

      • getJustifyFlag

        public java.lang.String getJustifyFlag()
        Returns the value of the justifyFlag. The column values will be printed using String.format and this flag will be used to right or left justify the text.
        Returns:
        The justifyFlag of this column
        See Also:
        justifyLeft()

      • justifyLeft

        public void justifyLeft()
        Sets justifyFlag to "-" so that the column value will be left justified when printed with String.format. Typically numbers will be right justified and text will be left justified.
